# Fumapress Content

- Every doc page needs frontmatter with at least `title`; add `description` for SEO and OG images.
- Optional sidebar: `meta.json` or `meta.yaml` per folder (`title`, `pages`, `root`, `icon`, …).
- Public engine docs under `content/docs/{api,guides,performance,reference}/` are GENERATED from `blit386/docs/` by
  `scripts/sync-docs-from-engine.mjs` (`pnpm run sync:docs`) – never hand-edit them, nor their section `meta.json`, nor
  `src/data/api-history.generated.json`. Edit the engine source, then re-sync.
- The engine repo's `blit386/docs/_sitemap.json` manifest decides which docs publish, and their URL, sidebar order, and
  subtitle. Add, remove, or reorder a page there, then run `pnpm run sync:docs`.
- Link API reference to site paths (`/docs/api/...`, `/docs/guides/...`) – the mirror is complete, so it cannot drift.
  Only engine docs omitted from the manifest (`developer-experience-guide.md`, `documentation-and-versioning-guide.md`,
  `tooling.md`, `voice.md`, `security/security-runbook.md`, `security/dependency-policy.md`,
  `security/audit-exceptions.md`, and the docs `README.md`) stay link-only on GitHub.
- Hand-authored and editable: `content/index.mdx`, `content/showcase.mdx`, `content/community.mdx`,
  `content/mcp-server.mdx`, `content/meta.json`, `content/blog/**`, and under `content/docs/`: `index.mdx`,
  `getting-started.mdx`, `faq.mdx`, `meta.json`.
- No emoji in content or UI strings.
- After editing links, run `pnpm run docs:links`.
